      DeadlineFull retellingГоловні тези1The Academy announced a second group of presenters for the 98th Oscars2Presenters include Javier Bardem, Demi Moore, Kumail Nanjiani, Maya Rudolph, Chris Evans, and Chase Infiniti3These presenters will appear at the Dolby Theatre on March 154More presenters will be announced before the ceremonyТеми:EntertainmentAwardsHollywoodUPDATED with latest additions: The Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences has opened the envelope on its second group of presenters for the 98th Oscars next month. Oscar winner Javier Bardem and past nominees Demi Moore and Kumail Nanjiani will take the Dolby Theatre stage on March 15 along with multiple Emmy winner Maya […]The Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences has announced its second group of presenters for the 98th Oscars, with Oscar winner Javier Bardem, past nominees Demi Moore and Kumail Nanjiani, multiple Emmy winner Maya Rudolph, Chris Evans of Captain America fame, and breakout star Chase Infiniti from One Battle After Another set to present at the Dolby Theatre on March 15. This announcement follows the Academy's strategy of revealing presenters in stages to build anticipation for the prestigious ceremony. The diverse lineup combines established Hollywood veterans with emerging talents, reflecting the broad appeal of the annual event that celebrates cinematic achievements across various genres and backgrounds. The Dolby Theatre in Hollywood will host the ceremony where these celebrities will assist in presenting the coveted golden statuette to deserving nominees in the film industry's most celebrated recognition of artistic excellence.Чому це важливоThis announcement is significant as it ramps up excitement for the 98th Academy Awards, the film industry's most prestigious event, by showcasing a blend of Hollywood royalty and rising stars. The selection of presenters like Javier Bardem and Chris Evans alongside newcomers such as Chase Infiniti demonstrates the Academy's strategy to appeal to a broad demographic and boost viewership ratings. For the nominees, the presence of high-profile presenters elevates the prestige of the moment, while for the audience, it promises an engaging broadcast filled with recognizable personalities.Контекст та передісторія•The Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences has been organizing the Oscars since 1929, making it the oldest and most prestigious award ceremony in the film industry.•The 98th Academy Awards are scheduled to take place on March 15 at the Dolby Theatre in Hollywood, California.•Javier Bardem is a previous Oscar winner, taking home the Best Actor award for his role in 'No Country for Old Men' in 2008.•Demi Moore is a veteran actress who has been nominated for an Oscar in the past and remains a significant figure in Hollywood.•The Academy frequently announces presenters in waves or stages to maximize media coverage and maintain public interest leading up to the live broadcast.Що даліThe Academy is expected to announce additional waves of presenters in the coming weeks to further build hype for the ceremony. On March 15, the event will commence at the Dolby Theatre, where these celebrities will present awards to the winners in various categories. Following the ceremony, analysts will review the viewership numbers to see if this diverse lineup of presenters successfully attracted a large audience.Часті запитанняQ1Who are the latest presenters added to the 98th Oscars lineup?The latest additions include Oscar winner Javier Bardem, nominees Demi Moore and Kumail Nanjiani, Emmy winner Maya Rudolph, Chris Evans, and breakout star Chase Infiniti.Q2When is the 98th Academy Awards ceremony taking place?The ceremony is set to be held on March 15 at the Dolby Theatre in Hollywood.Q3Why does the Academy release presenter names in stages?The Academy uses this strategy to build sustained anticipation and generate continuous media coverage in the weeks leading up to the event.Q4What film is breakout star Chase Infiniti known for?According to the announcement, Chase Infiniti is recognized as a breakout star from the film 'One Battle After Another'.Оригінал новини• DeadlineЗгорнутиUPDATED with latest additions: The Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences has opened the envelope on its second group of presenters for the 98th Oscars next month.Oscar winner Javier Bardem and past nominees Demi Moore and Kumail Nanjiani will take the Dolby Theatre stage on March 15 along with multiple Emmy winner Maya Rudolph, Captain America ‘s Chris Evans and One Battle After Another breakout Chase Infiniti.See below for the full list of presenters revealed so far; more will be announced ahead of the ceremony. Related Stories News Oscar Nominations 2026: ‘Sinners’ Leads With Record 16, ‘One Battle’ Next – The Complete ListЧитати повністю на джереліБільше новин про згадані персони🇺🇸Chase Infiniti, Demi Moore, Javier Bardem and Chris Evans Join Oscars PresentersPresenter26 лют.Watch Renate Reinsve Struggle With Stage Fright in ‘Sentimental Value’Academy Awards25 лют.What Do They Eat at Awards Shows (and Why Do We Care)?Academy Awards25 лют.🇺🇸Being BenicioAcademy Awards23 лют.BAFTAs Make the Oscars Messy, From Timothée Chalamet’s Shocking Loss to Sean Penn and Wunmi Mosaku Proving Supporting Races Are Anyone’s GameAcademy Awards22 лют.Читати оригіналПоділитися в XHillary Clinton posts opening statement for Epstein depositionПопередня🇺🇸 Всі новини‘John Proctor Is The Villain’ Playwright Kimberly Belflower’s YA Drama Lands At 20th Television With Kim Rosenstock As ShowrunnerНаступнаГраф пересіченьІнтерактивна візуалізація44
